                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/228: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-06-07T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1077. For Boyden from Department and Davis. B–47.</p>
                <p>Your 1218, May 29, B–105. Approve your statement provided that last clause first
                    paragraph statement reading “and that in any event it is hardly possible that
                    the United States shall share in such distribution” be omitted. It is believed
                    this clause not necessary, and advisable to leave it out.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
